Kapsabet and Nandi Hills towns will be the major beneficiaries after completion of the Sh6 billion Keben Water Reservoir.Governor Cleophas Lagat said the project, funded by the Africa Development Bank, will be implemented by the Water ministry.He said the national government has recognised the county s efforts to supply villages with clean water. Lagat said water access has increased from six per cent to 27 per cent. He said a feasibility study showed water from Keben dam could reach various towns by gravity, eliminating pumping costs.The construction is expected to start mid-next year, the governor said. Lagat said they will work with the national government to ensure the entire county has clean water for domestic use. We have de-silted several dams, which were covered by weeds, he said.